{{Infobox person | name = Darcy Rose Byrnes | image = | caption = | birth_name = Darcy Rose Byrnes | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1998|11|4}} | birth_place = [[California]], [[United States|U.S.]] | occupation = Actress & Singer | years_active = 2003âpresent |URL = http://darcy-rose.org/ }} '''Darcy Rose Byrnes''' (born November 4, 1998) is an [[United States|American]] [[child actress]] and singer. She is most famous for her role in the soap opera ''[[The Young and the Restless]]'' where she portrayed [[Abby Carlton]] from 2003 to 2008, she also appeared on ''[[The Bold and the Beautiful]]''. In 2010, she began portraying [[Acquaintances of Lynette Scavo#Penny Scavo|Penny Scavo]] in the seventh season of ''[[Desperate Housewives]]''.
==Career== Byrnes appeared in the direct-to-video film ''The Sparky Chronicles: The Map'' in 2003, the same year she landed a role in the soap opera ''[[The Young and the Restless]]'' as [[Abby Carlton]] from 2003 to 2008, during that time she also had a guest starring role in ''[[The Bold and the Beautiful]]'' for 8 episodes. Byrnes also has appeared in many different television shows including ''[[How I Met Your Mother]]'', ''[[Ghost Whisperer]]'', ''[[Cold Case (TV series)|Cold Case]]'', ''[[Dirty Sexy Money]]'' and ''[[House (TV series)|House]]''. She played Rebecca Knepp in the hallmark television movie, ''[[Amish Grace]]'' alongside [[Kimberly Williams-Paisley]].
